            <biogHist>
                <p>John MacNeil was born to Roderick MacNeil, crofter, and Mary née Gilles. In 1861
                    he was living with his wife Mary née McDonald in Bolnabodach, with his daughter
                    Marion (38) and a pauper visitor Peggy MacNeil (68). They were living in a house
                    with two rooms with windows. By 1871 John had become a widow, his wife dying on
                    17 June 1866 from old age, he also signed the death certificate. In March 1867
                    John meets Carmichael and tells him the story 'Each-drai Chlann Uisne'
                    [Eachdraidh Chlann Uisne]. At that time he still had a daughter Rachael (aged
                    28), a housekeeper, and two granddaughters Mary (11) and Elizabeth (5). John
                    died of old agein November 1875. His brother Alexander signed the death
                    certificate.</p>
